- (5) the pilose complex of S8 is rudimentary in 

P. sericea

, appearing as a longitudinal weak carina ending at basal 7/10 of sternite and with a field of long setae occupying the distal 3/10 of the sternite (
Fig. 17
). In 

P. calcarulata

the field of setae occupies the distal 2/10 and the sclerotized structure is shorter and T-shaped (
Fig. 10
);
